Equations can be solved by adding the same number, or term, to both sides of the equation, subtracting the same number (or term) from both sides of the equation or by multiplying both sides of the equation, or dividing both sides of the equation, by the same number or term.

review_3.column_1_text:
Each point on the line obeys the rule y = 2x.

The point (3, 6) will lie on the line.

Tip

Each point lying on a line obeys a particular rule. This rule is called the equation of the line.

success.question_text: If m is an odd number, which number will also be odd?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Problem Solving

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Multiplying any number by two will give an even number. So 2m will be even.

Multiplying an odd number by an odd number will give an odd number. So 3m will be odd.

Adding three to an odd number will make it even. So m + 3 will be even.

Subtracting one from an odd number will make it even. So m – 1 will be even.

If m is an odd number, 3m will also be odd.

review_2.column_1_text:
Tip

If in doubt when trying to determine what might happen to an expression under certain conditions, substitute a value into the expression. For example, in this question if m = 5, 2m = 10, 3m = 15, m + 3 = 8 and m – 1 = 4. Clearly the only odd value is 15.

success.question_text: The cost $C, of n pens at d cents each, would be given by which expression?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Generalised Arithmetic

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

With generalised arithmetic, do the question in exactly the same way as you would if you had numerical values. If unsure, put in values. For example, in this question if there were 3 pens at 50 cents each, the cost would be $1.50. Try each option to see which would have a value of 1.5 dollars.

Tip

If a pattern has been found in the differences between successive terms, you can use that pattern to find a particular value. For example, in this question the next difference in the y-values will be 3 × 18 = 54. The missing value will be 37 + 54 = 91.
